## Proposed Changes

### Phase 1: Solana Smart Contracts (Anchor)

#### [NEW] [Anchor.toml](file:///c:/Users/Tushar/rwa-solana/Anchor.toml)
- Workspace configuration for Anchor
- Program ID, cluster settings (localnet/devnet)
- Test and deploy scripts

#### [NEW] [Cargo.toml](file:///c:/Users/Tushar/rwa-solana/Cargo.toml)
- Rust workspace manifest
- Member: `programs/rwa-tokenization`

#### [NEW] [programs/rwa-tokenization/](file:///c:/Users/Tushar/rwa-solana/programs/rwa-tokenization/)

**State Accounts (PDAs):**
- `AssetAccount` вЂ” name, symbol, total_supply, available_supply, price_per_token, uri, authority, treasury, oracle_feed, is_active
- `UserOwnership` вЂ” owner pubkey, asset pubkey, shares_owned, purchase_price_avg, is_whitelisted
- `TreasuryVault` вЂ” asset pubkey, total_collected, yield_distributed, bump
- `WhitelistEntry` вЂ” user pubkey, is_verified, verification_timestamp, authority

**Instructions:**
| Instruction | Description |
|---|---|
| `initialize_asset()` | Admin creates a new tokenized property with SPL mint + metadata |
| `whitelist_user()` | Admin whitelists a KYC-verified user |
| `buy_shares()` | User purchases fractional tokens (checks whitelist, available supply) |
| `sell_shares()` | User sells tokens back to treasury |
| `transfer_shares()` | P2P transfer between whitelisted users |
| `distribute_yield()` | Admin distributes rental yield proportionally |
| `update_price()` | Update token price from Pyth oracle feed |

**Validation Rules:**
- Whitelist check on all buy/sell/transfer
- Overflow-safe arithmetic (`checked_add`, `checked_sub`, `checked_mul`)
- Ownership verification before selling
- Supply cap enforcement
- PDA seed derivation for deterministic addressing

**Oracle Integration:**
- Pyth `PriceUpdateV2` account consumed in `update_price`
- Feed ID configurable per asset
- Staleness check (max 60s age)

